
<html>
<body>
<div id="message">
  <div class="logo-bar">
    <div class="logo">
      <%= image_tag "odin_head_silhouette_2_777_216px.gif" %>
      The Odin Project
    </div>
    <div class="login-link">
      <a href="http://theodinproject.com/login">Login</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="top-box">
    <h1>
      Getting Started with The Odin Project
    </h1>
  </div>

  <div class="content-container">
    <div class="welcome-header">
      Welcome <%= @user.fname %>!
    </div>

    <div class="welcome-msg">
      It's great to have you with us while you learn web development!  It can be a bit overwhelming at first, so to get you started we've put together a few tips:
    </div>

    <div class="tip-wrapper">
      <div class="tip">
        <div class="tip-number">
          1
        </div>
        <h2>
          Plan out your strategy
        </h2>
        <p>
          Browse through the <%= link_to "roadmap of courses", curriculum_url %> and figure out how much time each week you'll be able to devote to learning so you can start to figure out your path forward.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="tip">
        <div class="tip-number">
          2
        </div>
        <h2>
          Dive into your first course
        </h2>
        <p>
          If you're brand spanking new to all this, start with <%= link_to "Introduction to Web Development", lesson_url(@starting_lesson) %>.  Otherwise, <%= link_to "Web Development 101", courses_url("web-development-101") %> is your best bet.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="tip">
        <div class="tip-number">
          3
        </div>
        <h2>
          Get help and work with others
        </h2>
        <p>
          You can leave questions in the <%= link_to "forum", forum_url %> or set up a time to pair program on a project with someone by using the <%= link_to "scheduler tool", scheduler_url %>.  Fill out your <%= link_to "profile", user_url(@user) %> to help others who might want to get in touch you.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="tip">
        <div class="tip-number">
          4
        </div>
        <h2>
          Tell your friends!
        </h2>
        <p>
          If you find the project helpful, please tell your friends about it so they can learn too!
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="additional-questions">
      <p>
        If you have any additional questions, check out our <%= link_to "Frequently Asked Questions", faq_url %> or feel free to reach out to <a href="mailto: contact@theodinproject.com">contact@theodinproject.com</a>.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="sendoff">
      <p>
        Best of luck with your learning journey!
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="signature">
      <p>
        Sincerely,
      </p>
      <p>
        Erik Trautman
      </p>
      <p class="founder">
        Founder, The Odin Project
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr>
  <div class="about-odin">
    <p>
      The Odin Project is a free and open-source curriculum for learning web development.  It charts a path through existing resources on the web so anyone in the world can develop a job-ready skillset and a professional portfolio of work without the loneliness and uncertainty of working on their own.
    </p>
  </div>
  
</div>

<style>
  body{
    font-size: 100%;
  }
  #message{
    width: 600px;
    border: 1px solid #666;
  }
  .content-container{
    padding: 2em;
  }
  .top-box{
    background-color: #013;
  }
  .top-box h1{
    text-align: center;
    color: white;
    font-size: 2em;
    padding: 2em 0;
  }


</style>

</body>
</html>